due to a lack of zoogeographic and morphological data, since extensive collections are unavailable. Furthermore, 
<bibRefCitation author="Foster, BA" journalOrPublisher="New Zealand Oceanographic Institute Memoir" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="1 - 160" refId="B24" refString="Foster, BA, 1978. The Marine Fauna of New Zealand: Barnacles (Cirripedia: Thoracica). New Zealand Oceanographic Institute Memoir 69: 1 - 160" title="The Marine Fauna of New Zealand: Barnacles (Cirripedia: Thoracica)." volume="69" year="1978">Foster (1978)</bibRefCitation>
suggested that a revision of the genus was called for since the variability of 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. japonica" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="japonica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">H. japonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as noted by Foster and tabulated by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1469-7998.1927.tb07432.x" author="Nilsson-Cantell, CA" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="743 - 790" refId="B47" refString="Nilsson-Cantell, CA, 1927. Some barnacles in the British Museum (Nat. Hist.). Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London 1927 (3): 743 - 790, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1469-7998.1927.tb07432.x" title="Some barnacles in the British Museum (Nat. Hist.)." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1469-7998.1927.tb07432.x" volume="1927" year="1927">Nilsson-Cantell (1927)</bibRefCitation>
, encompasses characters which have been used to distinguish several different species by other authors (e.g., 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. dubia" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="dubia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">H. dubia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Broch, 1922, 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. cornuta" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="cornuta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">H. cornuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Darwin, 1852, 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. indica" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">H. indica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Gruvel, 1901, 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. lankestri" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="lankestri">
